(Optional — calibrate based on data shared)

“For example, if your internal close rate is around [X%], we’d typically expect demand generated from our channels to convert in a similar range - maybe a 10–20% variance depending on deal cycle and ticket size. The goal is predictability, not over-promise.”


“Once that’s confirmed, we’ll assemble the right pod of internal and external talent — campaign ops, data, messaging — and put together the infrastructure needed to execute cleanly.


From there, we’ll outline a 90-day engagement anchored to a 45-day milestone, which we contractually obligate ourselves to. Even in a worst-case scenario, you’re still ROI-positive. That language will be blatantly clear in the scope so leadership can see that the engagement is fully de-risked.”


(Tone softens)

“If that’s something you and leadership feel could evolve into a scalable channel — quarterly, semi-annually, or annually — we’re happy to walk that path with you, align on risk tolerance, and define what tangible success looks like together.”


(brief pause, direct but calm)

“Any questions so far?”


We highly recommend asking some of these questions either now or when appropriate:


These questions help you gain a lot of ground during the buying process without sounding pushy upfront.

We need to understand the environment we’re selling in.


Keep them short and consequential (answers inform the SoW/EL and your tempo).


Approval Flow (choose 1–2):

“How do new engagements usually get greenlit internally?”
“Is there a standard review cadence (weekly exec, monthly finance) we should align to?”
“Who else will review the scope?”
Friction / Risk (choose 1–2):

“Have outside partners ever been slowed by legal or procurement? What helped?”
“Any compliance boundaries we should include?”

Soft → Direct Clarity Probes (use sparingly, by environment)

Soft: “Who typically needs visibility before you move forward on engagements like this?”
Moderate: “When you approved similar initiatives, who signed alongside you?”
Direct: “Who holds final signature on the EL and who authorizes payment timing?”

